# PostgreSQL + Feature Additions — Implementation Plan

Six features added on top of the existing client auth system.

---

## Key Design Decisions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **PostgreSQL via SQLAlchemy (sync)** — Using `SQLAlchemy 2.x` with `psycopg2-binary` (sync, no extra complexity). Since FastAPI runs in async context, we use `run_in_executor` for DB calls, keeping things simple without `asyncpg`.
>
> **No Django email backend** — This is a FastAPI app. We use Python's built-in `smtplib` + `ssl` with the same Gmail SMTP credentials provided.
>
> **OTP Flow** — OTP is a 6-digit code stored in the `email_otp` table with a 10-minute expiry. Registration is two-step: `POST /api/clients/send-otp` → `POST /api/clients/register` (with otp field).
>
> **Notifications** — Stored in PostgreSQL `notifications` table. Dashboard polls `GET /api/clients/me/notifications` every 30s. Unread count shown on bell icon.

